12. (a) Production, supply and distribution of goods, but not bounties on
production; price control and food control; adulteration of foodstuffs and other
goods;
(b) Imports into, and exports from, the Federation, but not bounties on
export;
(c) Insurance, including compulsory insurance;
(d) Auctions and auctioneers;
(e) Industries; regulation of industrial undertakings;
(f) Banking; money-lending; pawnbrokers.
